            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Didn't like the location\nThe school looks like it's inside of a forest or something and there's only one way to reach there with no proper road. There's huge stones (kids can fall, vehicle can lose balance) and sand (impossible to drive in rainy days) and huge gutter is open at the end of the road. So many rubber factory (cause smoke and smell) and wooden factories (noise pollution and small dust particles in air makes u cough)\nAbout School:\nSo small and gives a negative vibes. There's no place for assembly inside the school and no assembly or activities is organized for kids. Ain't property facility of helping desk or water, medicine, travel\nTeachers :\nSorry to say but they need to hire teachers with qualifications and teach your staff to be more humble and respectful towards kids and their parents. Main focus should be the window( aka helping window) . They just don't do the work on time and.. Yeah bring some chairs for parents to sit while they wait",
